ow that I've led successful attacks on everything in the zone except Ail the Elder and Tunare basically, I'm going to make a final opinion about this, this isn't binding just my advice on how 2 raiding parties can share the zone. Very simply, 1 raid goes north, the other south, the boundaries for pulling are tunare's tree and the portal, don't go past it..... well, doing that worked successfully yesterday anyway as got 2 raiding parties (around 48 people) and owned the zone, under this plan<br>
<br>
group 1 gets:<br>
<br>
kodiaks<br>
some flux<br>
glade stalkers<br>
some ferals<br>
the 3 named on west side<br>
some sylvs<br>
phase pumas<br>
essence cullers<br>
some tranquil treants<br>
Ail the Elder (heh gl, what an asshole)<br>
Fayl Everstrong<br>
<br>
group 2 gets:<br>
<br>
rolling plane steeds<br>
gale wolves<br>
some flux<br>
thiflings<br>
serene forest spirits<br>
some ferals<br>
some sylvs<br>
the essence around ancient totem<br>
undogo digolo<br>
treah greenroot<br>
rumbleroot<br>
prince thirneg<br>
keeper of the glades<br>
some tranquil treants<br>
ancient totem(drops nothing quest)<br>
tunarean earthmelder(drops nothing quest)<br>
guardian of takish (drops nothing quest)<br>
<br>
you also have to take into account that undogo and fayl summon essence cullers, treah summons sylvs, ail summons ferals and that PoG will go for one of the camps, anyway that's all I can remember from yesterday that's not confidential info, but it's very possible to be successful with multiple camps and I think the practice is useful to make sure the bigger stuff goes down more regularly. (I mean you don't need 2 camps to kill the big stuff, but it takes a LONG time to clear to them) <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
